OL,3,CMohamed Al Fayed 'manipulated' Harrods
OL,4,Cmanagers to hide alleged sexual abuse
OL,6,FA former Harrods director has
OL,7,Fdescribed how Mohamed Al Fayed would
OL,8,Fmanipulate managers to conceal his
OL,9,Falleged sexual abuse of dozens of
OL,10,Fwomen and girls.
OL,12,FJon Brilliant, who worked in Mr Al
OL,13,FFayed's private office for 18 months,
OL,14,Fsaid the former Harrods boss would
OL,15,Fsack those he could not control.
OL,17,FManagers were let go or quit so often
OL,18,Fthat a national newspaper began to
OL,19,Fpublish a regular count, which reached
OL,20,F48 in 2005.
