OL,6,FMr Brilliant, who was 36 when he
OL,7,Fjoined the firm in 2000, said the
OL,8,Fbusinessman would offer him cash to
OL,9,Ftry to compromise him.
OL,11,FHe told BBC News: "He was trying to
OL,12,Fget you to come back and say 'oh, I
OL,13,Fspent money on drugs or I spent money
OL,14,Ffrolicking, doing something that I
OL,15,Fshouldn't have been doing', and that
OL,16,Fhe would then use that information
OL,17,Fagainst you if you should ever turn on
OL,18,Fhim."
